cs.NE, cs.ET, cs.AR, cs.EM, cs.CV 

The paper discusses the implementation of deep learning models using hybrid CMOS-OxRAM devices, which involves both hardware and software aspects. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The use of OxRAM devices for computation and storage also suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to cs.ET (Emerging Technologies). The paper also involves the design and optimization of hardware architectures, which could fall under cs.AR (Hardware Architecture). Additionally, the paper discusses the classification and reconstruction of hand-written digits, which could be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the use of OxRAM devices for signal normalization could also suggest the paper belonging to cs.EM (Electromagnetics).
